    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-06T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-06T05:00:00-05:00" n="564"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d564">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94112/32: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tsingtao</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sokobin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tsingtao</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-06T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 6, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 6—9:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In view of the reported extension of the Japanese blockade,<note n="96"
                        xml:id="d564fn96">Effective September 5, noon.</note> the question has
                    arisen whether the Standard Vacuum Oil Company should make shipment of kerosene
                    and gasoline by Chinese vessels to Haichow, no other vessels being available.
                    The Consulate has brought to the attention of the American company the notice
                    served to Chinese and Japanese Governments on August 27<note n="97"
                        xml:id="d564fn97">For note to Japanese Foreign Office, see <ref
                            target="frus1931-41v01#pg_490">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 490</ref>; for note to Chinese Foreign
                        Office, see telegram No. 185, August 26, 8 p.m., to the Ambassador in China,
                            <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_289">p. 289</ref>.</note>
                    regarding <pb facs="0459" n="451" xml:id="pg_451"/> rights of American
                    Government and its nationals in respect of damages to or loss of American
                    property. Has the Department any instructions in respect to shipments of
                    American cargo from Tsingtao or information as to the reported exception of
                    Tsingtao from the blockaded zone and the implications of such an exception?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sokobin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
